EudraGMP is actually known as the EudraGMDP, which stands for European Union Drug Regulating Authorities Good Manufacturing and Distribution Practice database. This database is managed by the European Medicines Agency (EMA) and contains information about:

- Good Manufacturing Practice (GMP) certificates;
- Good Distribution Practice (GDP) certificates;
- Manufacturing and importation authorizations;
- GMP and GDP compliance reports; and
- Non-compliance statements.

It does not issue certificates of poor manufacturing practice. Rather, it records instances of non-compliance with GMP, which could involve sanctions such as revocations or suspensions of manufacturing authorizations. These non-compliance reports are issued when inspectors identify significant deviations from GMP standards during inspections.

In summary, the EudraGMDP serves as a transparency tool to help regulatory authorities and stakeholders track the compliance of organizations involved in the manufacturing and distribution of medicinal products within the European Economic Area (EEA).
